[SN]TITLE[SN]
Swapping hands 'boosts smartphone signal'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A new study suggests some phones perform better when held in one hand rather than the other.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
9 September 2016 Last updated at 17:53 BST
Prof Gert Pedersen from Aalborg University said phones had their antennas located where people naturally place their hands, affecting communications.
